The paper deals with the problem of coloring graphs, which is a fundamental topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus is on 3-colorable graphs, which are a special class of graphs that have received significant attention in the literature on graph theory and algorithms (cs.CC). The algorithmic approach is combinatorial, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper may have implications for the study of graph coloring from a game-theoretic perspective (cs.GT).
